question: Create a pie chart breakdown of successful vs failed payments
sql:
SELECT 
    CASE WHEN status = 'ACTIVE' THEN 'Successful' ELSE 'Failed' END as category,
    COUNT(*) as value
FROM subscription_payment_details
GROUP BY CASE WHEN status = 'ACTIVE' THEN 'Successful' ELSE 'Failed' END

question: Show me payment success rates for last 30 days
sql_query: SELECT COUNT(CASE WHEN p.status = 'ACTIVE' THEN 1 END) * 100 / COUNT(*) AS success_rate FROM subscription_payment_details p JOIN subscription_contract_v2 c ON p.subscription_id = c.subscription_id WHERE p.created_date >= DATE_SUB(CURDATE(),INTERVAL 30 DAY);

question: cli
sql_query: SELECT COALESCE(c.user_email,'Not provided') AS user_email,c.subscription_id,c.merchant_user_id,c.renewal_amount,c.max_amount_decimal,c.subcription_start_date,c.subcription_end_date,c.status,SUM(p.trans_amount_decimal) AS total_revenue FROM subscription_contract_v2 c LEFT JOIN subscription_payment_details p ON c.subscription_id = p.subscription_id AND p.status = 'ACTIVE' GROUP BY c.subscription_id,c.merchant_user_id,c.user_email,c.renewal_amount,c.max_amount_decimal,c.subcription_start_date,c.subcription_end_date,c.status LIMIT 20;

question: Show payment success rate for merchants with more than 1 transaction visually
sql_query: SELECT c.merchant_user_id,COUNT(CASE WHEN p.status = 'ACTIVE' THEN 1 END) AS successful_payments,COUNT(*) AS total_payments,(COUNT(CASE WHEN p.status = 'ACTIVE' THEN 1 END) / COUNT(*)) * 100 AS success_rate FROM subscription_payment_details p JOIN subscription_contract_v2 c ON p.subscription_id = c.subscription_id GROUP BY c.merchant_user_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 1 LIMIT 20;

question: number of merchants with more than 5 subscriptions and number of merchants with more than 5 payments
sql_query: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.merchant_user_id) AS merchants_with_more_than_5_subscriptions,(SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT merchant_user_id) FROM subscription_payment_details WHERE subscription_id IN (SELECT subscription_id FROM subscription_payment_details GROUP BY subscription_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 5)) AS merchants_with_more_than_5_payments FROM subscription_contract_v2 c GROUP BY c.merchant_user_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 5;
